                  . E. Arūdell B of Caūtorbury. but more ioyous is your message,
for wee of our owne naturall disposicion for the good will &amp; syngular
affection that you haue euer borne to vs, haue loued, embrased
and highly estemed you and all your doinges. Surely we woulde you
knewe with what sorowe and agony of mynde we haue borne your vexacions,
