likewise did his enemies, whiche bothe in puissance and courage were
nothyng to hym inferior. Then sodainly the trumpettes blew, the kynges
parte cried sainct George vpon them: The aduersaries cried Esperaunce

Percie, and so furiously the armies ioyned. The Scottes whiche
had the forward on the lordes side, entendyng to bee reuenged of their
