destroy duke Ihō of Burgoyn as the chief hed &amp; leader of that wicked
and great mischief: Wherby the realme was muche vnquieted &amp; more
decayed, and in maner brought to a final ruyne and vtter destruccion.
So Fraunce was inflamed and in euery part troubled with warr and
deuision, and yet no man would ether prouide in so great a danger, nor
once put furth their finger to hynder the mischief.
               
