                     IF I should here reherse what tounes wer conquered, what fortresses
were yelded, and who wer made capitaines of thesame, this Pamphlet
would turne to a volume more tedious then pleasaunt, and therfore
I ouer passyng small names and muche doyng, wil returne again
to the principall thynges touchyng the sequele of this history
                        •
                     . And
who so desireth to knowe all the circumstances of the deliuery, lette
hym ouerloke the Frenche writers, whiche to aduoyde shame confesse
