the Campe, where his enemies, the night before were lodged, and there
he founde many goodly peaces of ordenaūce, and inespecially one, called
Dygeon, named after the chief toune of Burgony, beside pauiliōs,
wine, beere, meale, and innumerable vitaill.
               
