his mariage, was by his counsaill admonished, to refuse and forsake so
innocent a creature, he, more moued with her faire face, then her womā
                  ly
wisedome, aunswered: that it was ynough for a woman, to iudge the
difference betwene the shurte and the dublet of her husbande, and to
