then were willyng, and more came willingly then were betrusted, some
came for feare, and some muche doughted to come, but the greatest
heddes wynked and sayd they could not, but they ment they would not
come. kyng Edward beyng in this perplexitie, and in diffidence of reysyng
any army, with such trusty frendes as he had departed into Lyncolnshyre,
consulting what was best to be done, but sodainly or he was
