had great plenty) as to serue their Artilarie, and to enclose their campe,
or otherwise to labor. And in all this army there was not one page.
               The kyng of England was at his arryuall highly displeased wyth
the duke of Borgoyn, which in the worde of a Prince, promised hym to
mete him at his landing with .ij.M. men of armes &amp; light horsemē, besyde
