was made Stauarde of the kynge his housholde, likewyse the Archebishop
of Yorke was deliuered: but Morton bishop of Ely, was deliuered
to the duke of Buckyngham to kepe inwarde, whiche sente hym to
his manoure of Brecknoke in Wales, from whence he escaped to kyng
