               The Frenchmen perceiuyng that the Englishmen intended to assaile
theim, moored their shippes as nye to the Castle of Brest as thei could,
and set bulwarkes on the land on euery side to shote at the Englishmen.
Also thei frapped together .xxiiii. greate Hulkes, that came to the Baye
for salt, and set theim on a rowe, to the intent that if the Englishe menne
would haue assaulted theim, thei would haue set theim on a fire, and let
theim driue with the streme emongest the Englishe Nauie. Prior Ihon
also laie still in Blacke Sable or Whitesande Baye, and plucked his
Galies to the shore, and sette his Basiliskes and other ordinaunce in the
mouthe of the Baye, whiche Baye was bulwarked on euery side, that by
water it was not possible to be wonne.
