renoumed. The Frenche kyng on his part ranne valiantly breakyng
speares egrely and so well ended his chalenge of Iustes, that he ought
euer to be spoken of. When the bend of the Duke of Burbon was of
their pretence of chalenge deliuered, thei toke leaue and departed.
