a barge, sir Thomas Louell desired him to sytte on the cusshyns and
carpet ordained for him, he sayd nay, for when I went to Westminster
I was duke of Buckyngham, nowe I am but Edwarde Bowhen the
mooste caitiffe of the worlde. Thus they landed at the Temple, where
