with Englishemens goodes at Margate within the kinges streames,
not without great slaughter on both parties, yet the Frenchemen were
C.lx. men, and of Spaniardes and Englishemen only .xxv.
               The kyng of Denmarke Cristianus came to se themperor his brother
in law beyng a stately prince, yet meanes was made that the lorde
Cardinal and he spake together without great signe of amitie.
