and almost all the people of Basse Bullein wer on the shore, that seyng
the garrison made them ready and bent their ordinaunce. Sir Willyā
Fitzwillyam hearyng the gunnes toward the hauenside knew wel that
Cristopher Coo was in his busines, and so encoraged euery man to do
