Then sir Robert Iernyngham with .lxxx. horsemen with all spede,
rode out of Calice to behold the compaignie of the Frenchemen. And he
sent furth his light horsemen, whiche met with the skourers of the Frēch
men, and because the Frenchemen semed a fewe in nombre, the Englishe
