his obedient subiect, to deliuer all the strong holdes into his captaines
handes: The Duke hearyng this counsaill, and willyng not to haue
the enmitie of the Emperiall capitaines, assented and deliuered to Dauall
all the fortresses that he had, except the castelles of Millain &amp; Cremona,
which he saied he kepte onely for the healthe of his body, because
he had ben long sicke.
