on his faithe and honoure. Well saied the Emperoure, if it bee
true that is reported, myne Uncle is not the Prince that I haue taken
hym for, and if he bee myne enemie, I muste withstande hym, and in a
greate fury, the Emperoure withdrewe hym from the Ambassadoure, to
his priuie chamber.
