to the peace, wherof we here deliuer you a writyng, which the Scottes
receiued, and at their next metyng thei saied, that the shippes to them
wer lawfull prises, by reason that therle of Anguishe, was maintened in
Englande, whiche is rebel to our kyng, and therle and you haue doen to
